[normal]The Energy Technologies Institute (ETI) is
[normal] a public-private partnership between global energy and engineering firms and the UK Government.
[normal]We carry out three key activities:
[normal]Our mission is to 
[normal]accelerate the development, demonstration and eventual commercial
[normal] d
[normal]eployment
[normal] of a focused portfolio of energy technologies which will increase energy efficiency, reduce greenhouse gas emissions and help achieve energy and climate change goals
[normal]In the last five years, the ETI has invested over £210m in 
[normal]52 
[normal]projects across nine techno
[normal]logy programme areas
[normal].
[normal] The technology project portfolio to 2017 
[normal]totals over
[normal] £400m of investment with four key aims to reduce the costs of generating energy, demand reduction, increasing investor confidence and increasing public acceptance and engagement.
[normal] 
[normal]Our industry and government partnership means we can share risk and create affordability for the development and demonstration of 
[normal]emerging 
[normal]new technologies
[normal] that have the potential to make a material impact on the future UK energy system
[normal].
