[normal]Recognising the need to focus and target investments to ensure value for money and leverage from public sector investments, the ETI’s techno-economic 
[normal]modelling and 
[normal]strategic 
[normal]analysis of the UK energy system
[normal] is a critical tool supporting effective innovation delivery.  The system is termed ‘ESME’ and is now used by DECC and the Committee on Climate Change to aid with planning and effective investment targeting.
