[normal]However, it is important
[normal] that the right steps are taken to ensure the cost of carbon reductions are affordable in the context of sustaining UK economic growth and industrial development.
[normal] 
[normal] Identifying and developing a series of options to support future energy system pathway decis
[normal]ions will be critical to delivering this. 
[normal]The ETI is
[normal] 
[normal]a core member of the Low Carbon Innovation Coordination Group (LCICG), which brings together the major public sector backed organisations that invest in low carbon innovation in the UK. 
[normal] 
[normal]The LCICG’s aim is to enhance the focus, coordination and delivery of support for innovation in low carbon technologies.  
[normal]Although each LCICG organisation has its own priorities for, and approach to, 
[normal]specific 
[normal]investment
[normal]s
[normal] in low carbon innovation, 
